WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.620
Hi, I'm Andrea, your virtual onboarding
specialist with the BMH Group.

2
00:00:05.160 --> 00:00:09.462
Thank you for being here. The fact that you
are watching this means you have made a

3
00:00:09.462 --> 00:00:11.180
decision to do something that

4
00:00:11.180 --> 00:00:14.760
matters. Not just a job. Not just a role.

5
00:00:15.320 --> 00:00:18.640
Something that genuinely changes people's
lives.

6
00:00:19.240 --> 00:00:23.160
We are glad you are with us at BMH Group,
and we mean that.

7
00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:27.920
Before we get into the training, we want you
to understand something important.

8
00:00:28.340 --> 00:00:30.860
The people you are going to be talking to
are not

9
00:00:30.860 --> 00:00:36.460
just names in a CRM. They are real people
carrying real burdens.

10
00:00:37.180 --> 00:00:38.780
And the way you show up for them

11
00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:42.920
matters more than any script or technique we
could ever teach you.

12
00:00:43.240 --> 00:00:45.200
The work you are stepping into is

13
00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:48.660
not what most people picture when they think
about real estate.

14
00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:51.760
You are not going to be showing homes.

15
00:00:51.760 --> 00:00:57.880
You are not going to be negotiating on
behalf of buyers who have options and time on

16
00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:02.465
their side. You are going to be talking to
families in the middle of some of the hardest

17
00:01:02.465 --> 00:01:03.640
moments of

18
00:01:03.640 --> 00:01:07.120
their lives. A foreclosure. A loss.

19
00:01:07.900 --> 00:01:10.480
A property that became too much to carry.

20
00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:12.500
A situation they have been trying

21
00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:16.160
to figure out for months with no clear
answer in sight.

22
00:01:16.620 --> 00:01:20.120
And you are going to help them find a way
through it.

23
00:01:20.120 --> 00:01:25.220
How? The BMH Group buys houses for cash, as
is.

24
00:01:25.740 --> 00:01:29.160
So a homeowner who needs speed and certainty
can move on

25
00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:32.780
without repairs, agents, or months of
waiting.

26
00:01:33.380 --> 00:01:36.520
That's the tool. This training is about how
you use it.

27
00:01:36.780 --> 00:01:38.280
That is fulfilling work.

28
00:01:39.340 --> 00:01:44.140
Real work. The kind that stays with you long
after the call ends and long

29
00:01:44.140 --> 00:01:45.400
after the deal closes.

30
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:48.600
There is a lot you will learn in this
training.

31
00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.340
The ideal prospect. The offer.

32
00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:54.080
The process. The objections.

33
00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:56.880
How to qualify a seller.

34
00:01:57.640 --> 00:01:59.540
How to present a cash offer.

35
00:02:00.280 --> 00:02:01.660
How to handle the moments

36
00:02:01.660 --> 00:02:03.660
when a conversation gets hard.

37
00:02:04.100 --> 00:02:08.060
You will also have a script and that script
is a valuable tool.

38
00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:14.420
It gives you structure, confidence, and a
clear path through every conversation.

39
00:02:14.900 --> 00:02:15.820
But here is the

40
00:02:15.820 --> 00:02:19.680
truth about what actually makes someone
exceptional at this work.

41
00:02:20.060 --> 00:02:22.320
It is not the script. The script tells

42
00:02:22.320 --> 00:02:28.080
you what to say. But the best reps know when
to put the script down and just listen.

43
00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:30.080
When to slow down.

44
00:02:30.940 --> 00:02:35.820
When to ask one more question instead of
moving to the next line.

45
00:02:36.020 --> 00:02:38.040
The most powerful thing you can

46
00:02:38.040 --> 00:02:43.300
develop is the ability to lead a homeowner
to the best possible path for their

47
00:02:43.300 --> 00:02:46.720
situation. Not our path. Maybe not our
company.

48
00:02:47.320 --> 00:02:50.640
Their path. When you sit in a conversation
with a distressed

49
00:02:50.640 --> 00:02:55.880
seller and you are genuinely focused on
understanding what they need and not just

50
00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:57.220
pushing them toward a yes,

51
00:02:57.780 --> 00:03:00.100
something shifts. They feel it.

52
00:03:00.420 --> 00:03:04.680
They trust you. And trust is what moves a
deal forward more than

53
00:03:04.680 --> 00:03:06.140
anything else ever will.

54
00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:10.700
The best closers at BMH Group are not the
ones who follow the script

55
00:03:10.700 --> 00:03:15.040
perfectly. They are the ones who know when
to set it down and just be present with the

56
00:03:15.040 --> 00:03:19.787
person on the other end of the phone. In the
training ahead, you will learn exactly who

57
00:03:19.787 --> 00:03:21.520
our sellers are, what we

58
00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:26.620
offer them, how our process works, and how
to handle the conversations that feel the

59
00:03:26.620 --> 00:03:29.880
hardest. But carry this with you through
every module.

60
00:03:30.100 --> 00:03:31.900
You are not here to sell.

61
00:03:32.180 --> 00:03:33.900
You are here to consult

62
00:03:33.900 --> 00:03:37.500
and provide options. Never pushy.

63
00:03:37.840 --> 00:03:42.300
Never desperate. You are here to help
families overcome difficult

64
00:03:42.300 --> 00:03:48.660
situations and walk away with clarity,
certainty, and the ability to move

65
00:03:48.660 --> 00:03:51.020
forward. That is the

66
00:03:51.020 --> 00:03:56.880
mission. Everything else is just the skill
set that makes you better at it.

67
00:03:57.320 --> 00:04:01.800
Welcome and we are
